A chaotic scene unfolded at Glasgow airport as a blazing jeep rammed into the terminal, prompting an evacuation.
British Prime Minister Gordon Brown confirmed it was a terrorist attack, leading to heightened security levels.
Following the incident, two suspects were arrested in connection with the London and Glasgow attacks.
The assailant, critically injured, was found with a suspicious device.
The government emphasized the importance of public vigilance and support for law enforcement.
The incident, now treated as a terrorist attack, resulted in airport closures and increased security measures across the UK.
